<http://model.geneontology.org/R-HSA-936440/R-HSA-936440>
        a       <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual> , <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GO_0032480> ;
        <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment>
                "As with other cytokine systems, production of type I IFN is a transient process, and can be hazardous to the host if unregulated, resulting in chronic cellular toxicity or inflammatory and autoimmune diseases. RIG-I-mediated production of IFN can, in turn, increase the transcription of RIG-I itself, thus setting into motion an IFN amplification loop, which if left unchecked, could become deleterious to the host. This module mainly focuses on the endogenous negative regulation of the RIG-I-like receptor (RLR) family proteins RIG-I (DDX58) and MDA5 (IFIH1)." ;
        <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label>
                "Negative regulators of RIG-I/MDA5 signaling" ;
        <http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/contributor>
                "Reviewed: Kawai, T, Akira, S, 2010-10-30" , "GOC:reactome_curators" , "Edited: Garapati, P V, 2010-08-02" , "Authored: Garapati, P V, 2010-08-02" ;
        <http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/date>
                "2026-07-02" ;
        <http://purl.org/pav/providedBy>
                "https://reactome.org" ;
        <http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref>
                "R-HSA-936440" ;
        <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#narrower>
                <http://model.geneontology.org/R-HSA-168928/R-HSA-168928> ;
        <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#note>
                "org.biopax.paxtools.model.level3.Pathway" .

